Vice President Mike Pence spoke with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan to discuss the impact of President Trump's South Asia strategy over the past year. They also talked about the current security situation in Afghanistan and efforts to initiate a peace process. Pence reinforced the U.S. and international commitment to partner with and support the Afghan government and security forces. They also discussed the upcoming parliamentary elections and the need for political inclusion to ensure the long-term stability and effectiveness of the Afghan government.